UC-01: User Registration
Actor: Passenger
Preconditions: Passenger has a smartphone or smart card; internet connection available.
Main Flow:
Passenger opens the Tap and Pay app.
Passenger selects “Register” and enters personal details (name, email, phone).
Passenger creates a secure password/PIN.
System validates input and creates a new account.
System confirms successful registration.
Alternative Flows:
2a. If email/phone already exists, system prompts for login or account recovery.
4a. If input validation fails, system requests correction.
Postconditions: Passenger account is created and ready for use.
UC-02: Login / Authentication
Actor: Passenger
Preconditions: Passenger has a registered account.
Main Flow:
Passenger opens the app and enters login credentials.
System validates credentials.
System grants access to passenger dashboard.
Alternative Flows:
2a. Invalid credentials → System prompts to retry or reset password.
Postconditions: Passenger is authenticated and can access system features.
UC-03: Wallet / Bank Account Linking
Actor: Passenger
Preconditions: Passenger account is active; passenger has a valid bank account or wallet.
Main Flow:
Passenger selects “Link Wallet/Bank Account”.
Passenger enters payment account details.
System verifies account via payment gateway.
System confirms successful linking.
Alternative Flows:
2a. Invalid account → System prompts to re-enter details.
3a. Verification fails → System shows error message.
Postconditions: Payment account is linked and ready for transactions.
UC-04: Tap-to-Pay Fare
Actor: Passenger, System
Preconditions: Passenger has linked payment account; bus fare reader is functional.
Main Flow:
Passenger taps NFC-enabled device or smart card on fare reader.
System authenticates payment.
Payment gateway authorizes transaction.
System deducts fare and confirms payment.
Alternative Flows:
2a. Authentication fails → System requests retry or alternative payment.
3a. Insufficient balance → System prompts user to add funds.
4a. Network failure → System queues transaction for later processing.
Postconditions: Fare is deducted and recorded; payment confirmation sent to passenger and conductor.
UC-05: Payment Confirmation Notification
Actor: Passenger, Bus Conductor, System
Preconditions: Tap-to-pay transaction initiated.
Main Flow:
System generates confirmation message.
Passenger receives visual/audio notification.
Conductor receives notification of successful payment.
Alternative Flows:
1a. Transaction fails → System sends failure notification.
Postconditions: Transaction status communicated to all actors; transaction logged in system.
UC-06: Payment Verification
Actor: Bus Conductor
Preconditions: Passenger has tapped and completed payment.
Main Flow:
Conductor scans passenger device or card.
System validates payment status.
Conductor allows boarding if payment is valid.
Alternative Flows:
2a. Payment not found → Conductor requests retry or directs passenger to add funds.
Postconditions: Passenger payment is verified; boarding decision recorded.
